//A soldier wants to buy w bananas in the shop.
He has to pay k dollars for the first banana, 2k dollars for the second one and so on (in other words, he has to pay i·k dollars for the i-th banana)
in this problem we have to find that how much money has to be borrowed by a person from his friend
to buy w bananas if he himself has n dollars.


7.Soldiers & Bananas
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;
int main() {
    int n,k,w;
    int sum = 0;
    cin>>k;
    cin>>n;
    cin>>w;
    for(int i=0;i<w;i++){
        sum = sum + (i + 1)*k;
    }
    if(n>sum){
        cout<<0;
    }
    else{
        cout<<sum - n;
    }
 
    return 0;
}
